This paper is primarily focused on evaluating the generalization ability of reinforcement learning agents, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also discusses the use of deep neural networks in RL, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The concept of procedural content generation is also mentioned, which is often studied in the field of game theory (cs.GT). Additionally, the paper proposes the use of roguelikes as a benchmark, which involves analyzing the structure and layout of game environments, a topic that falls under computer vision (cs.CV) and robotics (cs.RO).
